1️⃣ settings split (VERY IMPORTANT)

Instead of one huge settings.py, we use:

base.py → common settings

development.py → debug true

production.py → debug false, security settings

This is how real production apps are deployed.

2️⃣ apps folder

We separate by domain:

users → authentication related logic

todos → todo business logic

Each app is independent.

3️⃣ services.py

Instead of putting business logic in views, we separate it.

Example:

Creating todo logic

Complex validation

Custom calculations

This keeps views clean.

4️⃣ core folder

Reusable things go here:

Custom permissions

Pagination classes

Helper functions

This prevents duplication.